Articles.Content: I want to install mechjeb2 for 1.2 I heard that i got to have my mods installed by ckan. But what if there not available on ckan? And do i have to install the dev build of mechjeb2 from ckan?

You surely don't HAVE to install the DEV build of MJ with CKAN - But it's easier so why not ?

For the missing mod, yes you'll have to install them manually
CKAN is friendly with mods that are manually installed; He won't ever mess with them.

However the great benefit of using CKAN (only) is to not be able to install incompatible mods. (& to keep mods up-to-date. & never fail to install them properly)
This doesn't mean CKAN is not aware of them, just that he knows they'll cause trouble.
Check the "Incompatible" list on CKAN before installing mods manually - If they're there, you'll need to wait for the people who are taking care of it to update it for the current version of KSP

Or just don't use CKAN ; No mods require to be installed via CKAN

Edited October 28, 2016 by MrGeekArt

It is totally possible that mod you install manually conflict with other.
This is the reason I told you about the "incompatible" list on ckan :
Mods that do exist in that list should not be installed on your KSP, because they'll cause some problems. Installing them manually won't change the fact that there is bugs with them.

The only way to get some kind of warranty against conflict is to use ONLY ckan

And use patience® for the mods that are not yet compatible.

[1.2] Para-Sci High-Performance Atmosphere Pack v1.1 - 27 October 2016

or how do i find out if compatible

Hmm this is a special case.

This Atmosphere pack depend on EVE to work properly.

EVE is indeed on CKAN, but I can't find this pack - I guess you'll have to install this one manually.
But he IS compatible with KSP 1.2 so you're fine.

Make sure to have EVE installed 1st
Grab the files from here
Then open the archive. Inside is a "BoulderCo" folder;
Extract that into your GameData folder and overwrite the existing BoulderCo folder if there is one.
